Wade: The Group of Ministers on Foreign Investment had decided to recommend  
foreign equity participation upto 100% for trading in power sector, subject 
to prevailing laws. However, they left the final decision to the Union 
Cabinet. It is understood that a note supporting the recommendation of GoM is 
being put up for consideration of Union Cabinet. Since Power Minister is 
willing to support the proposal and Industry Minister is already OK with such 
proposals, I don't anticipate any problem at the Cabinet level. Let us wait 
and watch the developments. 

Seethayya
